text: Rannock is a rural community in the central north part of the Riverina. It is situated by road, about east of Methul and north of Coolamon. At the , Rannock had a population of 103 people. Rannock Post Office opened on 21 December 1908 and closed in 1970. ==Gallery== File:UnitingChurchRannock.jpg|Uniting Church Rannock ==Notes and references== Category:Towns in the Riverina Category:Towns in New South Wales Category:Coolamon Shire
